    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Compute the confidence interval for the correlation coefficient "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "statistic"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " with the given confidence level."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The confidence interval is computed using the Fisher transformation F(r) = arctanh(r) .  When the sample pairs are drawn from a bivariate normal distribution, F(r) approximately follows a normal distribution with standard error "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "1/sqrt(n - 3)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", where "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "n"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " is the length of the original samples along the calculation axis. When "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "n <= 3"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", this approximation does not yield a finite, real standard error, so we define the confidence interval to be -1 to 1."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
      "target": null,
      "title": null,
      "type": "Section"
    },
